# Tracker JSON (`#tracker-data`)

Canonical tracker: `docs/index.html`, embedded in `<script id="tracker-data" type="application/json">`.

## Immutable fields

Never reword or restructure:

- `id`, `type`, `parent`, `title`, `description`, `requirements`
- Acceptance criterion `statement` text
- `acceptance_criteria` array structure (during audit)

If something looks wrong, note it in `audit_notes` — do not edit the field.

## Status vocabulary

`TODO` | `IN_PROGRESS` | `IN_REVIEW` | `DONE` | `BLOCKED`

## Formatting

- Modify only the `#tracker-data` JSON block — never HTML/JS outside it
- Preserve JSON schema, key ordering, and formatting exactly
- `last_updated`: ISO 8601 date (e.g. `2026-06-27T00:00:00Z`)

## Story `verify` block

Each STORY should eventually have:

```json
"verify": {
  "files": ["path/to/changed/source"],
  "tests": ["test identifier"],
  "command": "command with machine-readable output"
}
```

`verify.files` must be real paths, not `(inferred)` guesses.
